<h3 class="date"><a href="/2008/apr/21/">&#x27a0;</a> April 21, 2008</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    <div class="flickrentry entry">
        <h4>NGINX requests - by day</h4>

        <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/groovymother/2431591623/"><img class="flickrphoto" alt="NGINX requests - by day" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3151/2431591623_f61494f929_m.jpg" height="134" width="240" /></a>

        <p>
            <p>A <a href="http://groovymother.com/2008/apr/21/book-indirectly-responsible-me/">blog post</a> I wrote last night ended up on the front page of <a href="http://www.reddit.com/">Reddit</a> this morning.  As of 2pm, I have had more unique visitors today than I had in January-March of this year combined!</p>

<p>My stack of <a href="http://www.nginx.net/">nginx</a>, <a href="http://httpd.apache.org/">Apache</a>, <a href="http://www.djangoproject.com/">Django</a> and <a href="http://www.danga.com/memcached/">memcache</a> all kicked in exactly as designed, and handled the flood of visitors without breaking (much) of a sweat, on a $25-a-month virtual server.</p>

<p>(Hat tip to <a href="http://simonwillison.net/about/">Simon Willison</a> for blogging about using this architecture. and inspiring me to preemptively deploy it on my own blog)</p>
        </p>

